<paragraph id="FE79CD20FFF0FFAAFC91738EDB83F782" blockId="65.[793,1399,1609,2049]" pageId="65" pageNumber="78">
The above female is in agreement with the original descriptions of neither of the two geographically closest species 
<taxonomicName id="39C6B6A3FFF0FFAAFCE473CDDB8BF882" baseAuthorityName="CAMERON" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[879,1011,1769,1793]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Tetrabothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubricollis">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FFF0FFAAFCE473CDDB8BF882" box="[879,1011,1769,1793]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="78">E. rubricollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="39C6B6A3FFF0FFAAFBBB73CDDCF1F882" baseAuthorityName="PACE" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[1072,1161,1769,1793]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Episkiodrusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="franzi">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FFF0FFAAFBBB73CDDCF1F882" box="[1072,1161,1769,1793]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="78">E. franzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and its spermatheca is different from those of 
<taxonomicName id="39C6B6A3FFF0FFAAFBE9722DDD45F8A2" baseAuthorityName="PACE" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[1122,1341,1801,1825]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Episkiodrusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neocoenonicacollis">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FFF0FFAAFBE9722DDD45F8A2" box="[1122,1341,1801,1825]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="78">E. neocoenonicacollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="39C6B6A3FFF0FFAAFC91720DDBDAF8C2" authorityName="PACE" authorityYear="2013" box="[794,930,1833,1857]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Episkiodrusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="veluticollis">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FFF0FFAAFC91720DDBDAF8C2" box="[794,930,1833,1857]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="78">E. veluticollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Nevertheless, this evidently new species is not described for want of males. The abdominal tergite and sternite VIII of the above female are covered by dense and coarse non-setiferous punctation, suggesting that the same is true also of other 
<taxonomicName id="39C6B6A3FFF0FFAAFB57728EDB1FF862" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Episkiodrusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FFF0FFAAFB57728EDD0EF842" box="[1244,1398,1961,1985]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="78">Episkiodrusilla</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, although this is not mentioned in their respective original descriptions.
</paragraph>
